      <elementaryExchange id="71980e11-f854-53ea-967e-4ad1919b218e" unitId="de5b3c87-0e35-4fb0-9765-4f3ba34c99e5" variableName="water_cooling_UNO_input" casNumber="007732-18-5" amount="0.0002872239208375742" sourceId="55b8a2ad-75e6-4ef8-83e1-3ce76899f59a" sourceYear="1998" sourceFirstAuthor="Sheenhan, J." elementaryExchangeId="fc1c42ce-a759-49fa-b987-f1ec5e503db1" formula="H2O">
        <name xml:lang="en">Water, cooling, unspecified natural origin</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m3</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated based on literature (Sheenhan, J., 18, An Overview of Biodiesel and Petroleum Diesel Life Cycles; Omni Tech International, 2010, Life Cycle Impact of Soybean Production and Soy Industrial Products), (Vionnet, S., Quantis Water Database - Technical Report, 2012). Assumed to have the same water use as "soybean methyl ester, at esterification plant". The process starts when refined oil enters the plant. It includes the processes: prepurification, deacidification, transesterification, destilation, etc. The process ends when methyl ester leaves the plant. It is assumed that 95% of water use is allocated to cooling water and 5% of water is allocated as process water.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.0002872239208375742" mu="-8.155248434434187" variance="0.01" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.061200000000000004"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="5" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="3"/>
        </uncertainty>
